<div id="gs-profile-email-settings">
  <h2>Your Email Settings</h2>
  <p>
    The <cite class="page">Change Email Settings</cite> page is used
    to 
    <a href="#gs-profile-email-settings-add">add an email address,</a>
    <a href="#gs-profile-email-settings-remove">remove an email
      address,</a>
    <a href="#gs-profile-email-settings-make-preferred">make an address
      a preferred delivery address</a> and
    <a href="#gs-profile-email-settings-make-other">make a preferred
      delivery address normal.</a>
  </p>
  <div id="gs-profile-email-settings-add">
  <h3>Add an Email Address</h3>
    <p>
      To add an email address to your profile carry out the following
      steps.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Visit <a href="/p">your profile.</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Click <samp class="link">Change Email Settings</samp>.
        The <cite class="page">Change Email Settings</cite> page will
        be shown.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click the <samp class="button">Add an addressâ€¦</samp> button. 
        The <cite class="dialog">Add an Address</cite> dialog will
        be shown.
      </li>
      <li>
        Enter your new address in the <samp class="entry">New
          Address</samp> entry.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click the <samp class="button">Add</samp> button. 
        An email will be sent to your new address.
      </li>
      <li>
        Follow the instructions in the email to <strong>verify</strong>
        that you control the address.
        <em>You must verify the address</em> before you can send
        or receive email from your new address.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong>
      You can only add a <em>new</em> address to your profile.
      You will see an error if you try to add an address that has
      already been added to any other profile.
    </p>
  </div><!--gs-profile-email-settings-add-->
  <div id="gs-profile-email-settings-remove">
    <h3>Remove an Email Address</h3>
    <p>
      To remove an email address from your profile carry out the 
      following steps.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Visit <a href="/p">your profile.</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Click <samp class="link">Change Email Settings</samp>.
        The <cite class="page">Change Email Settings</cite> page will
        be shown.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click the <samp class="button">Remove</samp> button next to
        the address you wish to remove.
        The button is only shown next to addresses you can remove
        (see the note below).
        After you click the <samp class="button">Remove</samp> button
        <ul>
          <li>The address will be removed from your profile.</li>
          <li>One of the addresses in your 
            <samp class="list">Other Addresses</samp> list will be made
            preferred delivery address if you have removed your only
            preferred address.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong>
      You can remove an address from the either the
      <samp class="list">Preferred Delivery Addresses</samp>,
      <samp class="list">Other Addresses</samp> or
      <samp class="list">Unverified Addresses</samp> lists.
      However, you can only remove an address from your profile if you
      have a different <strong>verified</strong> address.
      <a href="#gs-profile-email-settings-add">Add an address</a>
      if you only have one address and you wish to remove it.
    </p>
  </div><!--gs-profile-email-settings-remove-->
  <div id="gs-profile-email-settings-make-preferred">
    <h3>Make an Address a Preferred Delivery Address</h3>
    <p>
      To receive email at an address by default carry out the following
      steps.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Visit <a href="/p">your profile.</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Click <samp class="link">Change Email Settings</samp>.
        The <cite class="page">Change Email Settings</cite> page will
        be shown.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click and drag the address you want to receive email on by
        default from the <samp class="list">Other Addresses</samp> list
        to the <samp class="list">Preferred Delivery Addresses</samp>
        list.
        The selected address will become a preferred delivery
        address.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong>
      The <samp class="list">Other Addresses</samp> will only be shown
      when you have more than one verified email address.
    </p>
  </div><!--gs-profile-email-settings-made-preferred-->
  <div id="gs-profile-email-settings-make-other">
    <h3>Make a Preferred Delivery Address Normal </h3>
    <p>
      To stop receiving email at an address by default carry out the
      following steps.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Visit <a href="/p">your profile.</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Click <samp class="link">Change Email Settings</samp>.
        The <cite class="page">Change Email Settings</cite> page will
        be shown.
      </li>
      <li>
        Click and drag the address you no longer want to receive email
        on by default from the
        <samp class="list">Preferred Delivery Addresses</samp> list
        to the <samp class="list">Other Addresses</samp>
        list.
        You will no longer receive email at that address by default.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <p class="note">
      <strong>Note:</strong>
      You must always have at least one address in the
      <samp class="list">Preferred Delivery Addresses</samp> list.
      If only one address is listed in the 
      <samp class="list">Preferred Delivery Addresses</samp> list then
      you must first
      <a href="#gs-profile-email-settings-make-preferred">make another
        address a preferred delivery address.</a>
      Then you will be able to remove any address from the 
      <samp class="list">Preferred Delivery Addresses</samp> list.
    </p>
  </div><!--gs-profile-email-settings-make-other-->
</div><!--gs-profile-email-settings-->

